[1] Atyrau
Date: Thu 17 May 2007
Source: SNGNews, [translated by Assoc. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://sngnews.ru/articles/22/75048.htm>

The Ministry of Emergency Measures of Kazakhstan
reported that the number of domestic animals ill
with FMD [foot and mouth disease] has reached
786. Of these, 476 animals have been destroyed.
On 15 May [2007], FMD was found in 348 cattle
among the 1200 animals which were located at the
private farms in the village Sagyz of the
Kzylkoginskiy district in the Atyrau region. From
this group, 18 cattle were destroyed and buried in the special burial ground.
Diagnosis was confirmed in the Republic
Veterinary Laboratory during investigations of
blood samples. Quarantine measures were imposed
in the district and control and eradication
measures were applied. Ministry of the Extreme
Situation said that as of 16 May [2007], 1251
farms, 5315 cattle and 14 739 calves have been
inspected. It has been found that 641 heads of
cattle and 145 heads of calves have fallen ill,
while 431 heads of cattle and 45 heads of small
cattle have been destroyed. A total of 4287 heads
of cattle and 17 218 heads of small cattle have
been vaccinated. Quarantine and restrictive measures are being carried out.
--
